HEADWORD: Typhlosole
<hw>Typh"lo*sole</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ blind +
<?/ channel.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fold of the wall which
projects into the cavity of the intestine in bivalve mollusks, certain
annelids, starfishes, and some other animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Typhoean</ent>⟦br⟧
